wikipedia_page.main: William Birkmyre (1838 – 19 April 1900) was Liberal Member of Parliament (MP)  for Ayr Burghs from 1892 to 1895.

link_mentions.page: List of MPs elected in the 1892 United Kingdom general election

response: James Somervell (1845–1924) was Conservative MP for Ayr Burghs.  He won a by-election in 1890, but he lost his seat to William Birkmyre, the Liberal candidate, in the 1892 general election. He had earlier contested the 1885 general election for the Conservatives, but lost to the Scottish Liberal Party candidate Archibald Corbett.
